      <h2 class="section-title" id="theme">Conference theme for 2023</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="text-indent">
      <p>
        <strong>What does great software engineering culture look like, and how have Kiwis done it?</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        Culture is difficult to define and nuanced. Yet it is what attracts and retains engineering talent, as well as fosters innovation.
      </p>
      <p>
        We want to hear real life examples from NZ software engineers and engineering managers, about great engineering culture from different lenses.
      </p>
      <p>
        We’re especially keen on talks around:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>How different engineering practices influence culture (e.g. quality, data, front-end, open source, and etc.)</li>
        <li>Creating, contributing, maintaining, and scaling engineering culture (e.g. standardisation, architecture impacts, talent management, tech governance, community contribution, and etc.)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

